The paper focuses on image compressive sensing recovery, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of adaptively learned sparsifying basis via L0 minimization involves optimization techniques (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of split Bregman iteration, which is a method commonly used in image processing (cs.MM).
